{
  "doc_id": "52502",
  "text": "Living organisms show a striking diversity in size, life history, ecology, population structure, physiology, and cellular biology. This diversity propagates to the genome level: substantial between-species variations in base or amino acid compositions and in rates of sequence evolution have been documented [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Understanding the links between these two kinds of variations-phenotypic versus genomic-is an important goal of current molecular evolutionary research [CITATION_4] .",
